offtheroad users of diesel would be exempted 
from payment of the 151cent federal tax on april 1 under a senate 
finance committee amendment offered today 
the committee had approved the exemption last week but because 
of budget restrictions made the change effective oct 1 that 
would have required farmers fishermen and other offroad users to 
pay the tax for six months and then apply for a rebate early next 
year 
most of these users traditionally have been exempt from paying 
the tax a 1987 law that goes into effect april 1 requires that 
they pay the tax and later apply for a refund 
in introducing the new proposal today sen lloyd bentsen 
dtexas chairman of the finance committee said that exempting 
offroad users april 1 instead of oct 1 could be paid for by 
revising the requirements for corporations to make estimated 
incometax payments 
it is up to the house ways and means committee where tax bills 
must originate to determine whether the diesel provision is 
changed that panel has given no indication when it will consider 
the proposal meaning there is little chance it could become law by 
april 1 
