offices having let the twoyear statute of limitations expire on 
some 1600 complaints from oct 1 1986 to jan 31 1988 
but he said that in order to prevent such situations from 
recurring the agency needs more money 
i have been through the budget process seven times now and 
each time congress has appropriated less than what was requested 
by president reagan thomas said in his statement 
for example he said the agency sought 1934 million this year 
but received only 1798 million and it has been told its 
prospects for receiving a requested 1946 million in 1989 do not 
look good 
