the case with prejudice which means that mccloskey was legally 
the victor in the case 
mccloskeys lawyers meanwhile asked robertson to pay 42845 
in court costs now that the libel suit has been dismissed 
in a bill of court costs that was made public tuesday in us 
district court mccloskeys lawyer george lehner aksed for among 
other things 15794 to cover the cost of taking depositions from 
witnesses and 19458 for photocopying documents 
lehner said this figure included 16000 to make largesize 
trial exhibits of 30 to 35 documents 
robertsons lawyer douglas v rigler who has 11 days to file 
any opposition to the bill declined to say if he would make any 
objection i would want to discuss that with my client but just 
on first glance it looks extravagant 
