jesse jackson drew one in five white votes 
tuesday in connecticuts democratic primary far more than in 1984 
but too few to deny gov michael dukakis a big win exit polls said 
jacksons white support up from about 5 percent four years ago 
was bolstered by a nearly unanimous black vote wnbctv and abc 
