<TEXT>
latin america urged the united states 
on tuesday to end its economic blockade of panama while 
encouraging panama at the same time to make its democracy more 
effective 
the 26 member nations of the latin american economic system 
ended a twoday emergency conference convened at panamas request 
by condemning the us economic measures as contrary to 
international law and the charters of the united nations and the 
organization of american states 
the nations said they were opposed to foreign intervention in 
panama and asked washington to honor a treaty which turns full 
control of the panama canal over to panama in 1999 
we urge the us government to revoke immediately the coercive 
measures it has adopted against panama organization members said 
in a final threepage communique released late tuesday 
we reaffirm the sovereign right of all nations to decide their 
own economic social and political destiny in peace and liberty 
free from foreign pressure aggression and threats 
the organization based in caracas was founded in 1976 as an 
economic forum for latin american countries 
us economic action against panama is aimed at forcing the 
removal of gen manuel antonio noriega as chief of his nations 
defense forces and as de facto ruler of panama noriega is under 
indictment in the united states as a drug trafficker and 
moneylaunderer charges he denies 
the reagan administration has imposed economic sanctions and has 
backed moves by former panamanian president eric arturo delvalle to 
freeze panamanian accounts in us banks the united states still 
recognizes delvalle as president although he was ousted by noriega 
the latin american economic system took note of a promise by 
panama to deepen its democratic system 
the group said a request for economic aid by panamas 
cashstarved government will be considered with a spirit of 
solidarity by economic system members 
individual delegates clearly separated their support for the 
principle of selfdetermination from their position regarding 
noriega 
we have not come to defend a regime or even less a person who 
has been insubordinate to civil and constitutional authority 
perus foreign minister allan wagner told delegates tuesday 
our solidarity is with the people of panama 
he called for an end to panamas political crisis through free 
elections and the removal of any obstacles that prevent this clear 
expression of the will of the people of panama 
foreign minister jorge abadia arias of panama said monday his 
nation was fully committed to deepening panamas democratic 
system 
mexico and venezuela were among the individual nations monday 
that indicated their opposition to outside interference in panamas 
affairs without specifically mentioning the united states by name 
